# Contributing to QIH

Thank you for your interest in contributing to the QIH Project. This repository supports an open scientific framework for modelling health.

## Ways to Contribute

- **Suggest improvements** to the Colab simulator or theory documentation  
- **Report issues** related to clarity, logic, scientific grounding, or reproducibility  
- **Submit pull requests** with example scenarios, bug fixes, or usability enhancements  

## Guidelines

- Keep all code Pythonic and readable (PEP8 or near)
- Add clear units (e.g., J/K·s²) to any new functions or variables
- Include explanations and references when proposing theoretical changes
- Be respectful and constructive in discussions

## License

By contributing, you agree that your work will be licensed under the MIT License.

Thank you — we are grateful for your help advancing open science.
